{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge","doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge\/ScriptMessageHandler"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Executes the specified string as an asynchronous JavaScript function.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge\/ScriptMessageHandler\/callAsyncJavaScript(_:arguments:in:completionHandler:)"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brazekit\/braze\/webviewbridge\/scriptmessagehandler\/callasyncjavascript(_:arguments:in:completionhandler:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"callAsyncJavaScript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"functionBody"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"arguments"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"Any"},{"kind":"text","text":"] = [:], "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"webView"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)WKWebView","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"WKWebView"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"completionHandler"},{"kind":"text","text":": (@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultO","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Result"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"Any"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C13WebViewBridgeO20ScriptMessageHandlerC5ErrorO","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge\/ScriptMessageHandler\/Error","text":"Error"},{"kind":"text","text":">) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Void"},{"kind":"text","text":")? = nil)"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"functionBody","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The JavaScript string to use as the function body. This method treats"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the string as an anonymous JavaScript function body and calls it with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the named arguments in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"arguments"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"arguments","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A dictionary of the arguments to pass to the function call. Each key in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dictionary corresponds to the name of an argument in the functionBody","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string, and the value of that key is the value to use during the evaluation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the code. Supported value types are ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSNumber","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSString","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSArray","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSDictionary","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSNull","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". All items in an array or dictionary must also","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be one of the supported types.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"webView","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The web view in which the JavaScript function is executed. The web view must","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implement the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Braze\/documentation\/BrazeKit\/Braze\/WebViewBridge\/ScriptMessageHandler","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"name":"completionHandler","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A handler block to execute when script evaluation finishes. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method calls your block whether script evaluation completes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"successfully or fails. The block has no return value and takes the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"following parameter:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"result: The result of the script evaluation, or an error object that contains","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about the problem that occurred. If your function body doesn’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"return an explicit value, WebKit passes ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to your completion handler on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"success. If your function explicitly returns null, WebKit returns that value","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSNull"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function is a backport of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"WKWebView.callAsyncJavaScript(_:arguments:in:completionHandler:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method. It relies on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the script message handler to pass the result or error to the native side"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronously."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It differs from the WebKit method in the following ways:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No support for passing "},{"code":"NSDate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as an argument."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Errors are not wrapped in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"WKError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Don’t format the string in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"functionBody"},{"text":" parameter as a function-like callable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object, as you would in pure JavaScript. Instead, put only the body of the function in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string. For example, the following string shows a valid function body that takes x, y, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"z arguments and returns a result.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["return x ? y : z"],"syntax":"js"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your JavaScript code returns an object with a callable ","type":"text"},{"code":"then","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property, the function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calls that property on the resulting object and waits for its resolution. If resolution","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"succeeds, the function passes the resulting object to your completion handler. If","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"resolution fails, the function returns an error to your completion handler.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because this method calls your JavaScript code asynchronously, you can call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"type":"text","text":" on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects with a then property inside your function body. The following code example"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"illustrates this technique."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["var p = new Promise(function (f) {","  window.setTimeout(\"f(42)\", 1000);","});","await p;","return p;"],"syntax":"js"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"callAsyncJavaScript(_:arguments:in:completionHandler:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"callAsyncJavaScript"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"arguments"},{"kind":"text","text":": ["},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"Any"},{"kind":"text","text":"], "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"in"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)WKWebView","text":"WKWebView"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"completionHandler"},{"kind":"text","text":": (@"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultO","text":"Result"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"Any"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:8BrazeKit0A0C13WebViewBridgeO20ScriptMessageHandlerC5ErrorO","text":"Error"},{"kind":"text